  "original_title": "\u0d91\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbb\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 9110\u0d9a \u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Another compensation of 9110 lakhs from Express Pearl Insurance Company",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government of Sri Lanka has received an amount of 9110 lakh rupees from the ship's insurance company as the 3rd interim compensation amount to compensate the sailors who lost their lives due to the Express Pearl ship accident in 2021.",
        "Accordingly, Fisheries Minister Mr. Douglas Devananda instructed the officials including Ministry Secretary Mrs. Indu Ratnayake to distribute this amount among 15,032 identified fishermen in Gampaha, Colombo and Kalutara districts. Earlier also on two occasions Rs. 3480 lakhs and Rs. The Ministry of Fisheries arranged to distribute the interim compensation amounting to 3350 lakhs to these fishermen.",
        "As in the previous cases, the 3rd interim compensation amount is to be distributed through the Divisional Secretariat offices in the areas where the fishermen reside and with the payment of this 3rd interim compensation amount, all fishermen affected by the Express Pearl ship accident will be given Rs. . 80,000 to Rs. 240,000 in total has been awarded as compensation so far.",
        "After the Express Pearl shipwreck, a fishing ban was imposed in the area from Negombo to Panadura for the safety of fishermen, their gear and vessels and to prevent the possible effects of catching and consuming fish from the affected area. The number of fishermen who lost their livelihood due to this ban has been identified as 15,032."
      ],
